![Burning151.jpg](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/1604446084703-GU7WQ8VHUBAOCF6JSZZ3/Burning151.jpg)

Look up in the sky! It’s a bird! It’s a plane! No, its one of the biggest Superman fans in the Multiverse, **The Aspiring Kryptonian** herself, Tasmin! The Superman Superfan and collector has been making waves, being featured on the BBC network and DC Fandome amongst other things. In this episode, Tasmin jumps in the hot seat to talk all things Clark Kent/Kal El, including her favorite version of Lois Lane, whether or not Superman should have a secret identity, and why the world is big enough for multiple versions of the #ManOfSteel. Join us as we get candid about our fandom, and do a deep dive into what makes the Man of Steel Tasmin’s favorite superhero!

**Please** leave us a **_review_** on [**ITunes**](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/major-issues-podcast/id1321720972) so we can grow our audience and grow as podcasters! Rate us where ever podcasts are found. Don't forget to check out our [merchandise](http://www.teepublic.com/user/comicbookclique)! All episodes of Major Issues are brought to you by [**ComicBookClique.com**](../episode/update/id/Comicbokclique.com), the home for the latest and greatest things to come to comic books and comic book media.  
  
